## NotIterable type

Type utility that represents types that cannot be iterated over in `Object.keys`<!-- -->. Used to exclude specific types from iteration operations.

**Signature:**

```typescript
export type NotIterable = null | undefined | Map<unknown, unknown> | Set<unknown> | number | symbol | boolean;
```

## Example


```ts
type NonIterableValue = NotIterable;
// null | undefined | number | boolean | symbol | Map<unknown, unknown> | Set<unknown>

function processValue(value: NotIterable) {
  // Handle non-iterable values
}
```
